#: ../client/i18n.ts:143
msgid "Shogi with Chinese and Korean cannons"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/i18n.ts:144
msgid ""
"5x5 Shogi for more compact and faster games. There are no knights or lances."
msgstr ""
"5x5 Shogi für kompaktere und schnellere Partien. Es gibt keine Springer oder"
" Lanzen. "

#: ../client/i18n.ts:145
msgid ""
"A wild Shogi variant on a 5x5 board where pieces flip into a different piece"
" after each move."
msgstr ""
"Eine wilde Shogi Variante auf einem 5x5 Brett, wo Figuren nach jedem Zug zu "
"einer anderen Figur umgedreht werden."

#: ../client/i18n.ts:146
msgid ""
"3x4 game with cute animals, designed to teach children how to play Shogi."
msgstr ""
"Ein 3x4 Spiel mit niedlichen Tieren, entwickelt um Kindern Shogi "
"beizubringen."

#: ../client/i18n.ts:147
msgid "5x6 Shogi designed to introduce tactics with the generals."
msgstr "5x6 Shogi entwickelt um Taktiken mit den Generälen beizubringen."

#: ../client/i18n.ts:148
msgid ""
"A confrontational 7x7 variant with unique pieces each named after different "
"birds."
msgstr ""
"Eine konfrontierende 7x7 Variante mit einzigartigen Figuren benannt nach "
"Vögeln. "

#: ../client/i18n.ts:149
msgid ""
"Chinese Chess, one of the oldest and most played board games in the world."
msgstr ""
"Chinesisches Schach, eines der ältesten und meist gespielten Brettspiele der"
" Welt."

#: ../client/i18n.ts:150
msgid ""
"Xiangqi variant where one side has a chariot that can also move as a cannon "
"or horse."
msgstr ""
"Xiangqi Variante wo eine Seite einen Wagen hat, der sich auch wie eine "
"Kanone oder ein Pferd bewegen kann."

#: ../client/i18n.ts:151
msgid ""
"Korean Chess, similar to Xiangqi but plays much differently. Tournament "
"rules are used."
msgstr ""
"Koreanisches Schach. Ähnlich wie Xiangqi, spielt sich aber anders. "
"Turnierregeln werden verwendet."

#: ../client/i18n.ts:152
msgid "Compact version of Xiangqi played on a 7x7 board without a river."
msgstr ""
"Kompakte Version von Xiangqi, gespielt auf einem 7x7 Brett ohne Fluss. "

