#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:15
msgid "Is it rated?"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:17
msgid "How are scores calculated?"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:19
msgid ""
"A win has a base score of 2 points, a draw 1 point, and a loss is worth no "
"points."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:21
msgid ""
"If you win two games consecutively you will start a double point streak, "
"represented by a flame icon."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:23
msgid ""
"The following games will continue to be worth double points until you fail "
"to win a game."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:25
msgid ""
"That is, a win will be worth 4 points, a draw 2 points, and a loss will "
"still not award any points."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:27
msgid ""
"For example, two wins followed by a draw will be worth 6 points: 2 + 2 + (2 "
"× 1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:30
msgid ""
"(Janggi scores are different. A win has a base score of 7 points, and a loss"
" is worth no points. Point counting win and loss worth 4 and 2 points "
"respectively.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:32
msgid "Arena Berserk"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:33
msgid ""
"When a player clicks the Berserk button at the beginning of the game, they "
"lose half of their clock time, but the win is worth one extra tournament "
"point."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:35
msgid ""
"Going Berserk in time controls with an increment also cancels the increment."
" (1+2 is an exception, it gives 1+0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:37
msgid "Berserk is not available for games with zero initial time (0+1, 0+2)."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:39
msgid ""
"Berserk only grants an extra point if you play at least 7 moves in the game."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:40
msgid "How is the winner decided?"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:41
msgid ""
"The player(s) with the most points after the tournament's set time limit "
"will be announced the winner(s)."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:43
msgid ""
"When two or more players have the same number of points, the tournament "
"performance is the tie break."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:44
msgid "How does the pairing work?"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:45
msgid ""
"At the beginning of the tournament, players are paired based on their "
"rating."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:47
msgid ""
"As soon as you finish a game, return to the tournament lobby: you will then "
"be paired with a player close to your ranking. This ensures minimum wait "
"time, however you may not face all other players in the tournament."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:49
msgid ""
"Play fast and return to the lobby to play more games and win more points."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:50
msgid "How does it end?"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:51
msgid ""
"The tournament has a countdown clock. When it reaches zero, the tournament "
"rankings are frozen, and the winner is announced. Games in progress must be "
"finished, however they don't count for the tournament."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:52
msgid "Other important rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:53
msgid ""
"There is a countdown for your first move. Failing to make a move within this"
" time will forfeit the game to your opponent."
msgstr ""

#: ../client/tournamentFaq.ts:55
msgid ""
"Drawing the game before each player has moved 5 times will earn neither "
"player any points."
msgstr ""

